In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{1/2%cup}, @water{3/4%cup}, @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tsp}, and @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Remove from heat; cover to keep warm.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce.

Dice @Roma Tomato{1} into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Zest and quarter @Lime{1}. Peel and mince or grate @Garlic{2%cloves}. Drain @Black Beans{13.4%oz}.

== Salsa Fresca ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine tomato, scallion greens, lime zest, juice from half the lime, and a pinch of garlic. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

== Creamy Enchilada Sauce ==

In a separate #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine @Sour Cream{2%tbsp} with 1/4 of the @Enchilada sauce{10%oz}. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

== Beans ==

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{}, preferably nonstick, over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites, remaining garlic, and remaining Southwest Spice Blend. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add beans and remaining enchilada sauce. Cook, stirring, until liquid has absorbed, ~{3-5%minutes}. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

== Assembly ==

Once rice is finished cooking, stir in beans and a squeeze of lime juice. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Wash out pan.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for beans over medium heat. Once hot, crack @Eggs{2} into pan and cover. Fry eggs to preference. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

Cover bowl with sauce tightly with #plastic wrap{}; microwave until warmed through, ~{30-45%seconds}.

Divide rice and beans between #bowls{}; top with eggs, salsa, and sauce. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.